# 1. Copy this file to .env   →   cp .env.example .env
# 2. Put your real passphrase after the = below (no quotes needed in .env).
# 3. .env is gitignored, so the secret is never committed. You fill in .env,
#    NOT .gitignore — .gitignore just hides .env from git.
#
# WC_BETS_PASS encrypts the bet slip into data.json "betsEnc"
# (scripts/encrypt_bets.mjs, AES-GCM + PBKDF2). The public site decrypts betsEnc
# in-browser with this same phrase, so anyone you share it with can see the slip.
#
# Run the encrypt step with either:
#   node --env-file=.env scripts/encrypt_bets.mjs        # loads .env automatically (Node 20.6+)
#   WC_BETS_PASS='your passphrase' node scripts/encrypt_bets.mjs   # one-off inline
WC_BETS_PASS=
